net.hudup.core.parser

Class SnapshotParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.parser.BasicDatasetParser
      • net.hudup.core.parser.SnapshotParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, Alg, DatasetParser
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    JesterjokeParser, MovielensParser, SnapshotParserImpl

    public abstract class SnapshotParser
extends BasicDatasetParser
    There are two typical Dataset such as Snapshot and Scanner. Snapshot or Scanner is defined as an image of piece of Dataset and knowledge base (KBase) at certain time point. The difference between Snapshot and Scanner that Snapshot copies whole piece of data into memory while scanner is merely a reference to such data piece. Another additional Dataset is Pointer. Pointer does not contain any information nor provide any access means to dataset. It only points to another Snapshot, Scanner, or KBase.
    Although you can create your own Dataset, Dataset is often retrieved from utility class parsers that implement interface DatasetParser. Snapshot is retrieved from SnapshotParser. Scanner is retrieved from ScannerParser. Both SnapshotParser and ScannerParser implement interface DatasetParser. Pointer is retrieved from Indicator. Indicator is DatasetParser specified to create Pointer.
    Version:
    10.0

    Loc Nguyen
